Package com.telenav.kivakit.filesystem

Class Folder

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.broadcasters.Multicaster
com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.repeaters.BaseRepeater
com.telenav.kivakit.filesystem.Folder
All Implemented Interfaces:
SilentTryTrait, TryTrait, Broadcaster, Listener, Repeater, Transceiver, ChangedAt, CreatedAt, FileSystemObject, Receiver, Transmitter, NamedObject, ResourceFolder, UriIdentified, Comparable<Folder>
public class Folder extends BaseRepeater implements FileSystemObject, Comparable<Folder>, ResourceFolder, TryTrait
Folder abstraction that extends FileSystemObject and implements the ResourceFolder interface for filesystems. Consumes a FolderService supplied by a filesystem service provider. Filesystem service providers can be found in com.telenav.kivakit.filesystem.local (the local filesystem provider) and in the kivakit-filesystems module.

Factory Methods

  • parse(Listener, String, Object...) - A folder for the given string
  • from(URI) - A folder for the given URI
  • from(URL) - A folder for the given URL
  • from(java.io.File) - A folder for the given Java file
  • from(Path) - A folder for the given NIO path

Locations

  • current() - The current working folder
  • desktop() - The desktop folder
  • userHome() - The user's home folder
  • kivakitHome() - The KivaKit home folder
  • kivakitCache() - The KivaKit cache folder, normally ~/.kivakit
  • kivakitTemporary() - Folder where temporary files can be created
  • kivakitTest(Class) - Folder for test files for the given class

Properties

  • name() - The filename of this folder
  • disk() - The disk where this folder exists, if any
  • lastModified() - The last time this folder was modified
  • size() - The total size of this folder

Contents

  • files() - The files in this folder
  • files(Pattern) - The files in this folder matching the given pattern
  • files(Matcher) - The matching files in this folder
  • files(Matcher, Traversal) - The matching files in this folder found with the given Folder.Traversal type
  • folders() - The folders in this folder
  • folders(Matcher) - The matching folders in this folder
  • nestedFiles() - All nested files in this folder
  • nestedFiles(Matcher) - All matching nested files in this folder
  • nestedFolders(Matcher) - All matching nested folders under this folder
  • oldest() - The oldest file in this folder
  • oldest(Matcher) - The oldest matching file in this folder
  • temporaryFile(FileName) - A temporary file in this folder with the given name
  • temporary(FileName) - A temporary sub-folder with the given name
  • temporaryFile(FileName, Extension) - A temporary file in this folder with the given name and extension

Hierarchy

  • absolute() - This folder with an absolute path
  • path() - The path to this folder
  • parent() - The parent folder, or null if there is none
  • relativeTo(Folder) - This folder with a path relative to the given folder
  • relativePath(Folder) - The relative of this path with respect to the given folder
  • root() - The root folder of this folder
  • file(File) - The given file relative to this folder
  • file(String, Object...) - The file with the given name in this folder
  • file(FileName) - The file with the given name in this folder
  • file(FilePath) - The file with the given relative path to this folder
  • folder(Folder) - The folder relative to this folder
  • folder(String) - The folder with the given name in this folder
  • from(FileName) - The folder in this folder with the given filename
  • Folder(FilePath) - The folder with the given relative path to this folder

Operations

  • chmod(PosixFilePermission...) - Changes the access permissions of this folder
  • chmodNested(PosixFilePermission...) - Recursively changes the access permissions of this folder
  • clearAll() - Removes everything in this folder
  • clearAllAndDelete() - Removes everything in this folder and then deletes it
  • copyTo(Folder, CopyMode, ProgressReporter) - Copies this folder to the given folder
  • copyTo(Folder, CopyMode, Matcher, ProgressReporter) - Copies the matching files in this folder to the given folder
  • delete() - Deletes this folder if it is empty
  • mkdirs() - Creates this folder and any required parent folders
  • renameTo(Folder) - Renames this folder to the given folder
  • scheduleCleanUpOnExit() - Schedules this folder to be removed when the VM exits

Checks

  • ensureExists() - Ensures this folder exists or fails
  • exists() - True if this folder exists
  • isFolder() - True if this is a folder and not a file
  • isEmpty() - True if this folder is empty
  • isRemote() - True if this folder is on a remote filesystem
  • isLocal() - True if this folder is on the local filesystem
  • isMaterialized() - True if this folder exists locally
  • isWritable() - True if this folder can be written to

Conversions

  • asJavaFile() - This folder as a File
  • asUri() - This folder as a URI
  • asUrl() - This folder as a URL
  • absolute() - This folder with an absolute path
